l-winners-list-1057748/item/original-score-animated-film-1057703|title=Hollywood Music in Media Awards: Full Winners List|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=November 11, 2017|accessdate=November 18, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Online Film Critics Society]]\n| [[Online Film Critics Society Awards 2017|December 28, 2017]]\n| Best Voice-Over Performance\n| [[Alec Baldwin]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Online Film Critics Society Nominees \u2013 \u2018A Ghost Story\u2019 and \u2018mother!\u2019 Make the Cut|author =Clayton Davis| url=http://www.awardscircuit.com/2017/12/17/online-film-critics-society-nominees-ghost-story-mother-make-cut/|accessdate=December 18, 2017|publisher=AwardsCircuit.com|date=December 18, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Producers Guild of America Award]]\n| January 20, 2018\n| Outstanding Producer of Animated Theatrical Motion Picture\n| Ramsey Ann Naito\n| {{Nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Producers Guild Awards: \u2018Get Out,\u2019 \u2018Wonder Woman\u2019 Among Film Nominees|author =Dave McNary\t| url=https://variety.com/2018/film/awards/producers-guild-awards-movie-nominations-2018-1202654307/|accessdate=January 5, 2018|publisher=Variety|date=January 5, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[San Diego Film Critics Society]]\n| December 11, 2017\n| Best Animated Film\n|rowspan=\"2\" | ''The Boss Baby''\n| {{won|place=2|Runner-up}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sdfcs.org/2017-award-winners/|title=2017 San Diego Film Critics Society\u2019s Award Winners|work=[[San Diego Film Critics Society]]|date=December 11, 2017|accessdate=December 11, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Satellite Awards]]\n| [[22nd Satellite Awards|February 10, 2018]]\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Animated or Mixed Media Feature|Best Animated or Mixed Media Feature]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/dunkirk-the-shape-of-water-lead-satellite-award-nominations/|title='Dunkirk,' 'The Shape of Water' Lead Satellite Award Nominations|work = [[The Wrap]]|date = November 29, 2017|accessdate = November 29, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Saturn Awards]]\n| [[44th Saturn Awards|June 2018]]\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Animated Film|Best Animated Film]]\n| ''The Boss Baby''\n| {{Nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/saturn-awards-nominations-2018-black-panther-walking-dead-1202727752/|title=\u2018Black Panther,\u2019 \u2018Walking Dead\u2019 Rule Saturn Awards Nominations|last=McNary|first=Dave|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 15, 2018|accessdate=March 15, 2018|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6xwc1azco?url=http://variety.com/2018/film/news/saturn-awards-nominations-2018-black-panther-walking-dead-1202727752/|archivedate=March 15, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[Visual Effects Society|Visual Effects Society Awards]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" |[[16th Visual Effects Society Awards|February 13, 2018]]\n|Outstanding Animated Character in an Animated Feature\n| Alec Baldwin, Carlos Puertolas, Rani Naamani, Joe Moshier for \"Boss Baby\"\n| {{nom}}\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2018-visual-effects-society-awards-nominations-list-full-1067888|title=Visual Effects Society Awards: 'Apes,' 'Blade Runner 2049' Lead Feature Nominees|work=Hollywood Reporter|first=Carolyn|last=Giardina|date=January 16, 2018|accessdate=January 16, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|Outstanding Effects Simulations in an Animated Feature\n|Mitul Patel, Gaurav Mathus, Venkatesh Kongathi\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Franchise==\n\n===Sequel===\nOn May 25, 2017, [[Universal Pictures]] and DreamWorks Animation announced that a sequel is set to be released on March 26, 2021, with [[Alec Baldwin]] reprising his role.<ref name=\"sequel\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/boss-baby-2-alec-baldwin-release-date-dreamworks-animation-universal-1202102742/|title=Alec Baldwin Returns In \u2018The Boss Baby 2\u2019, Crawling To Theaters In 2021|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=May 25, 2017}}</ref> On May 17, 2019, it was announced that [[Tom McGrath (animator)|Tom McGrath]] will return as director and Jeff Hermann, who produces ''[[Bilby (film)|Bilby]]'' and ''[[Bird Karma]]'', as well as the upcoming short ''Marooned'', will produce the sequel.<ref>https://www.cartoonbrew.com/feature-film/boss-baby-2-will-be-tom-mcgraths-sixth-feature-film-at-dreamworks-174259.html</ref>\n\n===Television series===\n{{Main|The Boss Baby: Back in Business}}\nOn December 12, 2017, both [[Netflix]] and DreamWorks Animation announced the release of the TV series based off the film. ''[[The Boss Baby: Back in Business]]'' was released in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/she-ra-reboot-boss-baby-trolls-netflix-dreamworks/|title= \u2018She-Ra\u2019 Reboot, \u2018Boss Baby\u2019 Score Netflix Series Through DreamWorks Animation |date=December 12, 2017|accessdate=January 7, 2018|work=[[TheWrap]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|The Boss Baby}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.dreamworks.com/movies/the-boss-baby}}\n* [http://www.foxmovies.com/movies/the-boss-baby/ ''The Boss Baby''] at [[20th Century Fox|Fox Movies]]\n* {{IMDb title|3874544}}\n* {{bcdb title|166816}}\n* {{Rotten-tomatoes|boss_baby|The Boss Baby}}\n* {{Mojo title|bossbaby|The Boss Baby}}\n\n{{DreamWorks animated films}}\n{{Tom McGrath}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boss Baby}}\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:2017 3D films]]\n[[Category:2017 computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:2010s American animated films]]\n[[Category:2010s children's comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s spy films]]\n[[Category:20th Century Fox animated films]]\n[[Category:20th Century Fox films]]\n[[Category:American 3D films]]\n[[Category:American adventure comedy films]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy films]]\n[[Category:American computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:American spy films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:DreamWorks Animation animated films]]\n[[Category:DreamWorks Animation franchises]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Hans Zimmer]]\n[[Category:Films adapted into television programs]]\n[[Category:Films based on children's books]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Tom McGrath]]\n[[Category:Films featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:Films using computer-generated imagery]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Michael McCullers]]\n[[Category:Universal Pictures animated films]]\n[[Category:Universal Pictures films]]\n[[Category:3D animated films]]\n", "name_user": "Sojol khan", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eExternal links:Good)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Boss_Baby"}
{"title_page": "KOUA", "text_new": "\n\nKOUA is a [[London]] based fashion brand founded in 2014 by [[Erika alvarez|Erika Alvarez]].\n\n{{Infobox organization\n| name                = KOUA\n| founder             = Erika Alvarez\n| founding_location   = London\n| headquarters        = 20-22 Wenlock Road, London, N1 7GU\n| origins             = Mexico\n| website             = https://kouamexico.uk\n}}\n\n== Overview ==\nKOUA, also stylized KOUA Mexico, is a contemporary fashion brand that aims to promote [[Mexico|Mexican]] arts and crafts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kouamexico.uk/|title=KOUA Mexico|last=|first=|date=2016|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> They work with [[Indigenous peoples of Mexico]] to create fairtrade, ethically-sourced products, to preserve traditional Mexican embroidery and textiles, and to preserve the ancestral identity of Mexico's indigenous communities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://missportmanteau.com/interview-koua-mexzik/|title=INTERVIEW: Erika Alvarez of Koua|last=|first=|date=3 April 2017|website=Miss Portmanteau|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kouamexico.uk/koua-responsibility/|title=KOUA Responsibility|last=|first=|date=2016|website=KOUA|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://born.com/brand/QnJhbmQ6NDY5|title=Koua Mexico|last=|first=|date=|website=BORN|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> \n\nErika Alvarez, KOUA's founder, CEO and creative director, was born in Mexico.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gcu.ac.uk/alumni/profile/gculondon/erikaalvarez/|title=Erika Alvarez|last=|first=|date=|website=GCU Glasgow Caledonian University|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> She is also a fashion influencer and was 2018 winner of [[GCU London]] Alumna of the Year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gculondon.ac.uk/aboutus/alumni/alumnusoftheyearaward/2018winner/|title=2018 Winner|last=|first=|date=2018|website=GCU London|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yJN-OAcJDpk|title=GCU London presents Erika Alvares with Alumna of the Year|last=|first=|date=2018|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><br />\n\n== References ==\n", "text_old": "\n\nKOUA is a [[London]] based fashion brand founded in 2014 by [[Erika alvarez|Erika Alvarez]].\n\n{{Infobox organization\n| name                = KOUA\n| founder             = Erika Alvarez\n| founding_location   = London\n| headquarters        = 20-22 Wenlock Road, London, N1 7GU\n| origins             = Mexico\n| website             = https://kouamexico.uk\n}}\n\n== Overview ==\nKOUA, also stylized KOUA Mexico, is a contemporary fashion brand that aims to promote [[Mexico|Mexican]] arts and crafts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kouamexico.uk/|title=KOUA Mexico|last=|first=|date=2016|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> They work with [[Indigenous peoples of Mexico]] to create fairtrade, ethically-sourced products and preserve traditional Mexican embroidery and textiles and the ancestral identity of Mexico's indigenous communities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://missportmanteau.com/interview-koua-mexzik/|title=INTERVIEW: Erika Alvarez of Koua|last=|first=|date=3 April 2017|website=Miss Portmanteau|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kouamexico.uk/koua-responsibility/|title=KOUA Responsibility|last=|first=|date=2016|website=KOUA|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://born.com/brand/QnJhbmQ6NDY5|title=Koua Mexico|last=|first=|date=|website=BORN|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> \n\nErika Alvarez, KOUA's founder, CEO and creative director, was born in Mexico.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gcu.ac.uk/alumni/profile/gculondon/erikaalvarez/|title=Erika Alvarez|last=|first=|date=|website=GCU Glasgow Caledonian University|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> She is also a fashion influencer and was 2018 winner of [[GCU London]] Alumna of the Year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gculondon.ac.uk/aboutus/alumni/alumnusoftheyearaward/2018winner/|title=2018 Winner|last=|first=|date=2018|website=GCU London|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yJN-OAcJDpk|title=GCU London presents Erika Alvares with Alumna of the Year|last=|first=|date=2018|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><br />\n\n== References ==\n", "name_user": "RMJ13", "label": "safe", "comment": "Correct punctuation and grammar.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KOUA"}
